President Muhammadu Buhari has arrived his country home in Daura, Katsina State for Eid-el- Kabir celebrations. The President’s plane touched down at the Umaru Musa Yar’Adua Airport in Katsina at 5.15 pm. He was received by Governor Aminu Bello Masari, and other senior State government officials.   BREAKING: Panic as fire guts tank farm in Delta     JJC was not a nobody     EId-el-Kabir: Use religion to do good, Buhari urges…   On arrival in Daura, the President was received by the Emir, Dr Faruk Umar Faruk, members of the Emirate Council and other District Heads. According to a statement issued by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu, after the sallah celebration, the President, who is home with members of his family, will return to Abuja on Thursday, July 14, 2022.